peopleAlsoAsk.question: Can I use stamps that are 20 years old?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Stamps issued by the United States Postal Service NEVER expire! As long as it has not been cancelled, a stamp is valid for usage as postage!

peopleAlsoAsk.question: Are 10 year old forever stamps still good?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Yes, Forever Stamps, like all US postage stamps, retain their value forever (hence the name). You can use a $1 stamp from 1980 today if you so choose.
